==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Push button
<hw>Push button</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A simple device,
resembling a button in form, so arranged that pushing it closes an
electric circuit, as of an electric bell; -- called also
<altname>button</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pusher</ent>⟦br⟧
